# Deployment Guide (DPG)

## KSA-190: Auto-Linking Logic on KB Ingest

## Document Information

| Field | Value |
| --- | --- |
| Jira Ticket | KSA-190 |
| Version | 1.0 |
| Date | 2026-06-01 |
| Target Version | v1.13.1 |

## 1. Overview

This deployment adds the Auto-Linking feature to the Code Intelligence MCP Server extension.

**Affected Components:** - mcp-code-intelligence-nodejs (primary) - mcp-code-intelligence-kotlin (port) - mcp-code-intelligence-python (port) - VS Code / Kiro extension (packaging)

## 2. Pre-Deployment Checklist

| # | Item | Status |
| --- | --- | --- |
| 1 | All 39 automated tests pass | Done |
| 2 | SIT verified by user | Done |
| 3 | Code reviewed | Done |
| 4 | No breaking API changes | Confirmed |
| 5 | Backward compatible | Confirmed |

## 3. Deployment Steps

### 3.1 Build NodeJS Server

cd mcp-code-intelligence-nodejs
npm run build

### 3.2 Build Extension (VSIX)

vsce package

### 3.3 Install Extension

kiro --install-extension code-intelligence-1.13.1.vsix

### 3.4 Verify Installation

1. Open Kiro/VS Code
2. Run mem\_ingest with sample content
3. Verify response includes “Auto-linked: N edges”

## 4. Configuration

Auto-linking is enabled by default. No configuration changes required.

| Parameter | Default | Description |
| --- | --- | --- |
| autoLink.enabled | true | Master switch |
| autoLink.semantic.minScore | 0.75 | Cosine similarity threshold |
| autoLink.totalMaxEdges | 10 | Max edges per ingest |

## 5. Rollback Plan

### 5.1 Quick Rollback

Install previous extension version:

kiro --install-extension code-intelligence-1.13.0.vsix

### 5.2 Data Rollback

DELETE FROM knowledge\_graph\_edges
WHERE relation IN ('SIMILAR\_TO', 'SHARES\_ENTITY', 'SHARES\_TAG', 'TOPIC\_OVERLAP')
AND created\_at > '2026-06-01';

### 5.3 Disable Without Rollback

Set autoLink.enabled = false in config.

## 6. Post-Deployment Verification

| # | Check | Expected |
| --- | --- | --- |
| 1 | Extension loads without errors | No error in Output panel |
| 2 | mem\_ingest works | Entry created + auto-link count |
| 3 | mem\_graph auto\_link works | Backfill processes orphan entries |
| 4 | Existing KB data intact | Previous entries accessible |
| 5 | Performance acceptable | Ingest < 500ms |